            <summary><p>1 fol. on parchment; Sold 28 Oct 2020 as Lot 59; Qurʾānic Text: Q 27:57-27:70; 16 lines per page; Dimensions: 215 x 152mm. </p><p> </p><p>This manuscript probably belongs to the same Qur’an as 26 other  fragments, spread across a number of institutions and collections  worldwide. Some of these fragments were described in great detail, see  for example the catalogue entry for <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/11/vers/116?handschrift=1397">HC.MS.2017.0009</ref> by Marcus Fraser. </p><p> </p>For a more detailed description, please visit <ref target="https://www.christies.com/en/lot/lot-6282131?ldp_breadcrumb=back">Christie's website</ref>.<p/></summary>
